        <content><![CDATA[<p>Your Java code will typically use the <a href="%(link0)">OpenCms Java API</a>. For development, we recommend the&nbsp;<a href="%(link1)">Eclipse IDE</a> with&nbsp;<a href="%(link2)">Gradle</a> for build automation. If configured correctly, gradle will automatically handle all dependencies of your code to the OpenCms core.</p>
<p>In the remainder of the section, we describe how to set up your own Eclipse project.</p>
<p class="alert alert-info">We assume you already have installed Eclipse and Gradle as described <a href="%(link3)">here</a>.</p>]]></content>
